            <div class="col-md-8">
                <p>
                    <ul style="content: '\f067';">
                        <li>
                            Most of our forms are “Single Name Entry” forms. Just type “Name” and press “Enter” key, and you are done with your work.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>  Step 1 (Once in Lifetime)</b>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Lists -> Account
                            <br/>
                            * "Accounts" are organizations or entities which are your clients or potential clients.  For Example: “Acme Hospitals, Delhi” or “Sharda Enterprises”.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Lists -> Contact
                            <br />
                            * Contacts are the persons whom you talk to in your respective “Account”. A contact can be a Doctor, Purchase Manager or MD etc. For Example: “Dr. James Smith”, “Sunil Kumar Sharma” etc.
                            <br/>
                            * When creating “Contact”, it is recommended that you link it with an “Account”.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Step 2 (Once in a month in most cases)</b>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            “Lead” or “Opportunity”
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            * Lead – If you are approaching new person/entity for the first time and don’t know if it’s qualified to be your customer, then it’s a “Lead”. For example: You get a list of numbers you need to call, these are your leads. Go to “Sales -> Lead” and “Create” your leads in application
                            <br/>
                            * You can “Convert ” a “Lead”  to “Opportunity” after it qualifies from “Lead Detail” page.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Opportunity – A qualified “Lead” is an “Opportunity”. 
                            <br />
                            * For example:  A medical sales professional approaching a new hospital. Its an opportunity for him because a hospital is qualified lead and he knows that it’s a potential customer. He can directly create an “Opportunity” from “Sales - Opportunity” your opportunity in application
                            <br />
                            * In “Opportunity Detail” page, scroll to bottom and add products in “Opportunity Line Items” which you expect from this opportunity.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b>Step 3 (Just two clicks daily, no typing)</b>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            * Navigate to “Dashboard”. Find you respective “Lead” or “Opportunity”, and click on it to open “Lead Detail” or “Opportunity Detail” page.
                            <br/>
                            * In “Lead Detail” or “Opportunity Detail” page just click on “Create Task” link to create automatically linked related “Tasks”.

                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
